ZH: 我披上了一件厚厚的外套来应对寒冷的冬天。
EN: I put on a thick coat to cope with the cold winter.

ZH: 她披上了一条漂亮的围巾来搭配她的新外套。
EN: She wrapped a beautiful scarf around to match her new coat.

ZH: 他披上了一件温暖的毛衣，准备出门散步。
EN: He put on a warm sweater and prepared to go for a walk.

ZH: 妈妈披上了一件围裙开始做晚饭。
EN: Mom put on an apron and started cooking dinner.

ZH: 我们应该披上面罩来防止感染病毒。
EN: We should wear face masks to prevent virus transmission.

ZH: 她披上了一条长裙，显得非常优雅。
EN: She put on a long dress and looked very elegant.

ZH: 在演出前，演员们都会披上服装来扮演角色。
EN: Before the performance, the actors would put on costumes to portray their characters.

ZH: 天黑了，他披上了一件厚实的棉袄。
EN: It got dark, and he put on a thick cotton-padded coat.

ZH: 他披上了游泳圈，以防止沉入水中。
EN: He put on a lifebuoy to prevent himself from sinking in the water.

ZH: 她披上了一条围巾，不仅保暖又时尚。
EN: She wrapped a scarf around her neck, not only for warmth but also for fashion.

ZH: 母亲披上了一件新买的披肩，去参加晚宴。
EN: Mother put on a newly bought shawl and went to the dinner party.

ZH: 她披上了一件羽绒服，准备迎接寒冷的冬天。
EN: She put on a down jacket, preparing for the cold winter.

ZH: 在冬天，我喜欢披上一条毛毯看电影。
EN: In winter, I like to wrap a blanket around and watch movies.

ZH: 她披上了一件厚厚的围巾，以防止寒冷的风吹进领口。
EN: She wrapped a thick scarf around to prevent the cold wind from blowing into her collar.

ZH: 在下雨天，我们都会披上雨衣。
EN: On rainy days, we all put on raincoats.

ZH: 外婆披上了她编织的毛衣，给我保暖。
EN: Grandma put on the sweater she knitted to keep me warm.

ZH: 我们需要披上雨披，以免淋湿了衣服。
EN: We need to put on raincoats to avoid getting our clothes wet.

ZH: 她披上了一件风衣，以应对刮风的天气。
EN: She put on a windbreaker to cope with the windy weather.

ZH: 他披上了斗篷，看起来像个魔法师。
EN: He put on a cloak and looked like a magician.

ZH: 雪花飘落时，我披上了一件厚厚的大衣。
EN: When the snowflakes fell, I put on a thick coat.
